100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On January 26, 1926, the British Empire faced growing tensions as a general strike loomed in South Wales due to labor disputes in the coal industry. Meanwhile, in the United States, the Senate continued its deliberations on the proposed naval expansion bill, sparking debates over national security and military preparedness. In Egypt, unrest escalated as nationalist leaders called for independence from British rule, signaling a rising tide of anti-colonial sentiment across the globe.
